# Agentforce Metadata — Operational Rules

How to work on Agentforce subagents/topics (`GenAiPlugin`), planners, and invocable actions without burning tokens or fighting the Metadata API. Pairs with `salesforce-deploy-gotchas.mdc`.

## Source of truth
- **Read `{{BUILD_DOC_PATH}}` first, every time.** It has the verbatim label/description/scope/instruction strings for each task. Re-deriving them from Help articles or MCP wastes tokens. Only reach for external docs when the build doc has an explicit gap.
- **Do NOT load generic Agentforce topic-design / instruction-library docs for `GenAiPlugin` tasks.** They don't affect `GenAiPlugin` metadata shape and add token cost with zero payoff.
- The **repo XML is the human-readable source of truth** for instruction order.

## Deploy & verify
- **Deploy by named component only:** `--metadata "GenAiPlugin:{{PLUGIN_API_NAME}}"`, one flag per plugin. Never deploy by folder.
- **Do not retrieve-to-verify `GenAiPlugin`.** The org normalises instruction `sortOrder` to `0`; a retrieve only rewrites it and marks the file `Changed`. Trust the deploy output table (`State: Created`/`Changed`).
- Use lexicographically ordered `developerName` values (`{{TOPIC}}_Instruction_01` … `_NN`) so Builder shows steps in order regardless of `sortOrder`.
- **Never** retrieve `GenAiPlugin`/`GenAiPlannerBundle` with no member or a wildcard — it pulls 200+ unrelated files. Retrieve named components after you know the API name.

## Authoring
- Author `GenAiPlugin` with `pluginType: Topic`, `canEscalate: false`, and only the `genAiPluginInstructions` the build doc literally specifies — do not invent instructions from narrative hints.
- Link topics to the agent in legacy Agentforce Builder, not via a `plannerField` element (fails parse in API v{{API_VERSION}}).
- `GenAiPlugin` is **not** queryable via Tooling API — verify via the deploy table or the Builder Topics tab, not SOQL.

## Invocable actions (Apex)
- Pin `<apiVersion>{{API_VERSION}}</apiVersion>` in every `*.cls-meta.xml` to match `sfdx-project.json`'s `sourceApiVersion`.
- Ship the test class in the **same** named deploy as the class it covers.
- `--test-level RunSpecifiedTests` silently skips on sandboxes — run `sf apex run test --synchronous` separately; trust the per-class coverage row, not `Org Wide Coverage`.

## Security
- **Never echo org credentials.** `sf org list --json` and `sf org display --json` include access tokens — never paste them into chat or docs.

